   In Pennsylvania a degree from an
 accrediated engineering school, a ten
 dollar fee, and a favorable reply from
 five qualified references, qualifies one
 for an "Engineer-In-Training" certifi-
 cate. Four years later, after having
 practical engineering experience, the
 "Engineer-In-Training" becomes eli-


