   No doubt all of us have seen a carburetor.
Probably very few, however, have had the op-
portunity to see just what happens in a carbure-
tor while it is functioning. Maybe late this se-
mester you will be able to see right into the heart
of a carburetor while it is in operation. If you
do, it will be due to the efforts of two Aeronau-
tical students, Bob Frayer and Tom Sullivan.
   Bob started the project by cutting rectangular
 holes into a Carter Carburetor and removing the
 vaporizing venturi tubes and their supports. Tom
 is now completing the project by inserting plexi-
 glass windows into the carburetor so that the
 operation within it can be seen. In addition Tom
 is replacing the metal venturi tubes and braces
 with ones of plexiglass so that the vaporization
 and flow of the fuel can also be seen. All the
 plastic parts had to be machined very carefully
