             ERNEST WILLIAMS
  Another project whose results will benefit
future students was the construction of two Wag-
ner Type or Tension Field beams. The project
was started by Dom Maglore and completed last
fall by Ernie Williams who constructed the beams.
  The beams are primarily used in aircraft struc-
tures. Their chief advantage is that they are
light and very strong in bending, while being
weak in torsion. The beam has a web which
buckles when the beam is loaded in bending, en-
abling the beam to carry the shear load in the
web as a tension load. By this means it is able
to resist the shear loading in the web and by de-
sign is inherently strong in bending.
  In the future the beams can be used for dem-
onstrating to classes the manner in which this
important type beam carries and distributes the
loads placed upon it.
  The application of theoretical knowledge to a
