  Disclosing the vast scope of its re-
search and engineering in developing
electronic picture tubes for color tele-
vision, the   Radio  Corporation   of
America announced in October, 1951,
that it has built five types of tri-color
tubes, each one capable of operation
on all known television systems.
  The five types of tubes illustrate
basic designs covering a wide range
of principles. Among the principles


